# RemindMe India — Frontend Coding Rules

## PROJECT CONTEXT
React + Tailwind frontend on Vercel for RemindMe India (B2C + B2B WhatsApp reminder service).
Site: remindmeindia.site. Repo: github.com/ayushmalviya1806/remindme-india-frontend (main branch).
Tech: React, Tailwind CSS, Lucide React icons, React Router DOM.

## CRITICAL BUILD RULE
Vercel breaks on ESLint warnings. Always run CI=true npm run build before showing diff.
Zero warnings tolerated.

## STYLE SYSTEM
- Tailwind utility classes only
- Custom colors: rm-primary (green-dark), rm-green (light green), rm-text, rm-muted, rm-beige, rm-surface, rm-wa
- No inline styles unless using CSS variables
- Hinglish-friendly copy (mix Hindi-English naturally)
- Lucide React icons only (no other icon libraries)

## CODING STYLE
- PowerShell syntax (Windows): semicolons (;) for command chaining
- No backup files (.bak, .backup, copies)
- Surgical FIND/REPLACE only — no full file rewrites unless requested
- Single commit per logical change
- React functional components with hooks only

## OUTPUT FORMAT
For every change:
1. Show diff
2. Run CI=true npm run build and confirm zero warnings
3. Wait for user approval before commit/push
4. Never auto-commit, never auto-push

## BRAND POSITIONING
- "India's smartest WhatsApp AI assistant" (NEVER "first" — legal risk)
- "Meta Verified Business" (trust signal)
- "DPDP Act 2023 Compliant" (regulatory signal)
- "Made with heart in Indore, India"
- NEVER expose vendor names (OpenAI, GPT-4, AWS, etc.) on customer-facing pages

## CURRENT STATS (truth, use these only)
- 1,500+ reminders delivered
- 343+ users
- 98% delivery rate
- Free tier: 10 reminders/month
- Pro: 99 per month
- Student: 49 first month (STUDENT50 code)

